Dear Plainedge Community Members,

Our Board of Education and Central Administration understand the importance of a graduation ceremony for our students and want to honor their achievements. The Elementary Fifth Grade Moving up Ceremonies, the Middle School Eighth Grade Moving Up Ceremony and the Plainedge High School Graduation Ceremony have been postponed to this Summer 2020. All ceremonies will be held at the Edward Byrne Memorial Field located at Plainedge High School.

Sincerely,
Plainedge Public Schools

#Plainedge2020
#WeArePlainedge
#WeAreAllInThisTogether

We‚Äôd like to invite you this evening to the honor the Class of 2020 across Long Island, especially our seniors here at home. You can participate by turning on your porch lights at 8:20PM, taking pictures of our seniors, and posting them to social media with the hashtags #BeTheLight and #WeArePlainedge.

Additionally, schools across Long Island will turn on stadium lights at 8:20pm (20:20 in military time) tonight. We will join in by doing so at our high school athletic complex. This tribute will be live streamed at https://video.plainedgeschools.org/Watch/classof2020. Please tune in from 8:20-8:40 to view this moment honoring our seniors.

Stay safe, be well. #WeArePlainedge

post_text:
Good Morning,

Communication between school and home is extremely important at Plainedge Public Schools. To provide valuable ongoing correspondence, the district utilizes the School Messenger system to deliver emails, phone calls and text messages with important information about events, school closings, safety alerts and more. In order to participate in text messages, you must indicate your willingness to receive messages to your phone. The process is simple and only takes a few seconds to complete.

Simply text ‚ÄúY‚Äù or ‚ÄúYes‚Äù to 67587 or open your camera and hover over the QR code.

You will want to repeat the opt-in process for any wireless numbers that you wish to include.

Sincerely,
Plainedge Public Schools

The Town of Oyster Bay invites our Plainedge families to a special NBA (G league) event when the Long Island Nets take on the Canton Charge on Monday, January 20th at 3 PM at the Nassau Veterans Memorial Coliseum! The town has made 500 tickets available to our community members at no cost, first come, first served.

To reserve your free tickets, use the promotional code PLAINEDGE and click here: http://bit.ly/LINetsNight.

Below are the directions to receive your QR code on your mobile device:

Go to NYCBLIVE.COM/MYTIX on your cell phone.

Go to Manage Tickets. Log in with the same credentials as your Ticketmaster account. An account must be created to access your tickets. Then, you will be able to accept your tickets.

If you need any more help, please contact Central Office between the hours of 8 AM to 4 PM at (516) 992-7453. #WeArePlainedge

November 11, 2019 at 2:41 AM ¬∑

This past Friday @PlainedgeTV students from Plainedge HS were given the opportunity to interview US veterans. This was part of a larger event, organized by the Schwarting PTA where veterans read to elementary students, patriotic short stories. The elementary and HS students alike were actively engaged, collectively intrigued, and visibly grateful. The collaboration for this event across buildings and community was truly inspiring. Remember to thank those who served our country, not just today but every day. Veterans Featured: Joseph Tilleli, John Cronin, Stephen Paskor, Ivan Montanez, Kevin Hasson, Michael Kinsley. HS Student Videographers and Interviewers Julia DeMicco, Kaley DeMicco, Tara Colonel, Kyle Gustafson, Daniel Freeman, Joseph Frank, Michael Falacara, Emma Kelley

Happy Veteran‚Äôs Day
- Mr. White & Mr. Lombino

post_text:
Congratulations to Our 2019 Reader Leader Award Recipients!

Today, Superintendent Salina, along with Assistant Superintendents, Lisa DePaola and Cathy Honeyman, visited with our Summer 2019 Reader Leaders to present them with their awards for achieving excellence! To be a Reader Leader our elementary school students needed to complete a minimum of three books overthe summer and complete a Reflection Sheet for each book read. Many of our students read in excess of 10 Books each! There were over 250 students that achieved this designation! Wow! Congratulations to all our students and their families!

Warm Regards,
Ed Salina, Superintendent of Schools
text:
Congratulations to Our 2019 Reader Leader Award Recipients!

Today, Superintendent Salina, along with Assistant Superintendents, Lisa DePaola and Cathy Honeyman, visited with our Summer 2019 Reader Leaders to present them with their awards for achieving excellence! To be a Reader Leader our elementary school students needed to complete a minimum of three books overthe summer and complete a Reflection Sheet for each book read. Many of our students read in excess of 10 Books each! There were over 250 students that achieved this designation! Wow! Congratulations to all our students and their families!

Warm Regards,
Ed Salina, Superintendent of Schools

Plainedge High School's Graduation Ceremony is tonight at the Hofstra University Arena!

The event begins at 7 PM, but students must arrive at 6:30 PM!

We will be livestreaming the event via our YouTube channel http://bit.ly/PHSGraduation at 6:45 PM.

Be sure to click on "'LIVE NOW' Plainedge Public Schools Livestream" to watch the event. #WeArePlainedge

The 5th Grade Moving Up Ceremonies for our elementary schools will be held on Tuesday, June 25th!

Eastplain Elementary will be held at 9:15 AM in the Plainedge High School auditorium.

Charles E. Schwarting Elementary will be held at 1 PM in the Plainedge High School auditorium.

John H West Elementary will be held at 11 AM in the Plainedge Middle School auditorium.

If you are unable to attend in person, we will be live streaming each event via https://video.plainedgeschools.org/movingup #WeArePlainedge
